    "summary": "Experienced general counsel with demonstrated agility across multiple regions and sectors. Recognized by Legal 500 on the 2023 GC Powerlist for BeNeLux, as General Counsel EMEA for HOYA Corporation, Samantha oversees the legal function for the global company throughout EMEA. She partners with the business to drive growth and create value by supporting business initiatives and development enabling HOYA Corporation\u2019s strategic vision.\n\nPreviously a Partner at Dentons, Samantha specialized in corporate law and has over two decades of experience advising international, pan-African and domestic clients on public and private M&A and equity and debt capital across multiple jurisdictions. She has also advised clients on the optimization of their in-house legal function. Her prior experience includes her role as an investment banker with Rothschild and a subsequent return to law as VP Group Assistant General Counsel for AngloGold Ashanti. She has practiced law with top tier and magic circle law firms in Johannesburg and London. \n\nSamantha was previously a committee member for WomenLEAD (a global Dentons empowerment initiative), was named a Best Lawyer in South Africa 2021, co-led the African Legal M&A Team of the Year 2019 and while at Rothschild was an Approved Executive for the JSE. She is a dual-qualified lawyer, admitted both in South Africa and England & Wales. Samantha was awarded the Mandela Cambridge Scholarship by, and is a Fellow of, the Cambridge Commonwealth Trust and completed her LLM at Queens\u2019 College, Cambridge, England in 2000, having previously studied law and history at the University of Cape Town, South Africa.",
